snippet.textDisplay: There’s no doubt that Allah Rakha Rehman has established himself as one of most innovative and creative musicians of India. He is rightly credited for bringing a revolution in Bollywood music. Having said that, and being a fan of his earlier work, his Coke Studio India work is very disappointing. snippet.textDisplay: "Salutations to him, who couldn't bear the lord's grief, that is Abbas, who did not put his life before his brother!""I am Saki with a pure heart, with every breath, I say, Ali, Ali, I am sufi with a pure heart, with every breath I say, Ali, Ali"The piece belongs to the family of Ustad, handed down through generations.  It is a tribute to Abbas who laid down his life for his step-brother, Husain, in a battle nearly 1370 years ago at Karbala in Iraq.  Husain was the son of the daughter of Prophet of Islam.  He was Ali's son revered by almost all Muslim sufi traditions. Husain, along with nearly 18 youths of his family, and 54 other supporters was slaughtered when he refused to give his allegiance to a tyrant.  Women in his convoy, including his sister, and kids were taken prisoners.  This event if commemorated by Shia Muslims every year.  However, the story is so powerful, it moves most people regardless of religion and race.  There is a wealth of literature, poetry, and music related to Karbala.
snippet.textOriginal: "Salutations to him, who couldn't bear the lord's grief, that is Abbas, who did not put his life before his brother!""I am Saki with a pure heart, with every breath, I say, Ali, Ali, I am sufi with a pure heart, with every breath I say, Ali, Ali"The piece belongs to the family of Ustad, handed down through generations.  It is a tribute to Abbas who laid down his life for his step-brother, Husain, in a battle nearly 1370 years ago at Karbala in Iraq.  Husain was the son of the daughter of Prophet of Islam.  He was Ali's son revered by almost all Muslim sufi traditions. Husain, along with nearly 18 youths of his family, and 54 other supporters was slaughtered when he refused to give his allegiance to a tyrant.  Women in his convoy, including his sister, and kids were taken prisoners.  This event if commemorated by Shia Muslims every year.  However, the story is so powerful, it moves most people regardless of religion and race.  There is a wealth of literature, poetry, and music related to Karbala.
